race.comment: GOPHER FRANK (4) has been freshened and looks well placed here. He's a multiple track and distance winner that is drawn to get the right run here. He looks the horse to beat on his best form. MAGIC FIELD (1) is another that saves his best for this track and distance. He's never missed a place in five runs over the Mt Gambier short course. The claim should help his chances and he won't be far away. NANKEEN (5) is getting closer to another win, with placings at two of her last three starts over this trip. Both ZOULAR (3) and FALL OF ROME (6) can mix their form, although are capable of running a cheeky race if things go to plan.
